The makings of “Sally Owens.” I begin with chalk pastel on paper in black and white. I then scan it and make small corrections in Photoshop. Then add digital color with my ipad using Procreate and Photoshop. If you’d like to see a more detailed step by step post, check out my Patreon. Ideation and Visual Storytelling
Online Mentorship with Visual Arts Passage @visualartspassage 
 
This summer I'm teaching with Visual Arts Passage!

This Ideation course explores the art of developing a compelling and engaging story, a critical component of visual narrative. This skill can be applied to all corners of the creative industry. Each class includes lectures, demonstrations, critiques, or projects.

#DragonCon2023 #DragonConArtShow #DragonConArtShow2023
Dragon Con is in full swing. Come say Hi 👋. I’m booth 104 at the Art Show bottom floor of the Hyatt.
There are so many talented cosplayers at @dragoncon! I love love love the vibe here in Atlanta. 🍻

Sorry for the radio silent since Dragon Con. Once we returned home our household tested positive for COVID. I’ve been recovering 🤒. At day 6 I’m nearly feeling normal. My head still feels like it’s underwater, but no other issues. My husband and toddler are doing fine too. I wanted to tell everyone who stopped by my booth, THANK YOU! I had so many wonderful conversations. DC always brings people to me who really make me feel seen. Thank you for supporting my work and my vision. It lifts me up in such a positive way. I look forward to next year! #dragoncon #dragonconartshow @dragoncon
